cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for short term load forecasting, which is a problem in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. RNNs are a type of neural network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the challenges in training RNNs, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper applies the reviewed models to real datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
